<P><H1 align=center>ADD / EDIT GROUP CONNECTIONS</H1>
<P></P>
<P><FONT color=red><STRONG>NOTE: </STRONG>fields shown in red are mandatory and must be completed to 
proceed</FONT>           </P>
<H3>Connection owner: </H3>if the application is in a sole name, this field will 
be pre-populated with the applicant’s name. If it is a joint application, select 
the applicant with the connection from the drop-down list 
<P></P>
<P><H3>Account type: </H3>select the account type from the 
drop-down list – this could be a mortgage, investment, life policy or pension
<P></P>
<P><H3>Account number: </H3>complete this field if the account 
number is available 
<P></P>
<P><H3>Any additional account holders?: </H3>if it is a joint 
account, click on ‘Yes’ then complete the field below with the details. If it is 
a sole account, click on ‘No’
<P></P>
<P><H3>Another: </H3>if there is more than one connected 
account, click ‘Another’ and add the next account
<P></P>
<P><H3>OK: </H3>clicking ‘OK’ returns to the main <A HREF="HELP_DC020.asp">‘Group 
Connections’ screen (DC020)</A>
<P></P>
